Lisa Siobhan McCloskey, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Robert James McCloskey of Chevy Chase, Md., and George Joseph Brodmerkel 3d, a son of Dr. and Mrs. Brodmerkel Jr. of Pittsburgh, were married yesterday at the Shrine of the Most Blessed Sacrament in Washington. The Rev. Percival D'Silva officiated at the Roman Catholic ceremony. Andre Taylor McCloskey was her sister's maid of honor. William Nadel was the best man.

Mrs. Brodmerkel, 24 years old, and her husband graduated from Middlebury College. She teaches the first grade at Beauvoir, the Washington Cathedral elementary school. The bride's father, a former Foreign Service officer, was an Ambassador to Cyprus, the Netherlands and Greece. He is the editor of Mediterranean Quarterly: A Journal of Global Issues, which is to publish its first issue next month.

The bridegroom, 24, is a freelance film producer in Washington. His father heads the gastroenterology department at Allegheny General Hospital in Pittsburgh.